### `index.astro`

Finally, create the main `index.astro` file to bring everything together:


---
import Menu from '../components/Menu.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import Testimonials from '../components/Testimonials.astro';
import Pricing from '../components/Pricing.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Real Estate Landing Page</title>
</head>
<body>
  <Menu />
  <Hero />
  <Testimonials />
  <Pricing />
  <Footer />
</body>
</html>


This setup provides a basic structure for a real estate landing page with a menu, hero section, testimonials, pricing plans, and a footer. You can further customize and expand each section as needed.